

Hush CMS
========

Hush CMS has been installed, by default the administrative area is disabled for security purposes. To enable the administrative area, change and un-comment the username and password lines in config/hush.yml


Hush CMS depends on the haml gem and the tiny_mce plugin, ensure these are installed:
  
  haml:
    gem install haml
  

  tiny_mce:
    (git w/ submodule support)
    git submodule add git://github.com/kete/tiny_mce.git vendor/plugins/tiny_mce

    (regular)
    script/plugin install git://github.com/kete/tiny_mce.git
 

    (finally) 
    rake tiny_mce:scripts:install



